     <span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-08-02-pb-0339">[339<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-08/ADMS-06-08-02-pb-0339.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
     <div class="docback">
      <div class="note-alert"><p>The content of all or some notes that appeared on this page in the printed volume has been moved to the end of the preceding document.</p></div>
      <div class="note-source" id="PJA08d229sn1">
       <p>
        <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> and enclosure</span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</span>
       </p>
      </div>
      <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d229n1-ptr" id="PJA08d229n1">1</a>
       <p>This invoice is reproduced in vol. 3 of <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Adams Family Correspondence,&lt;/i&gt; ed. L. H. Butterfield and others, Cambridge, 1963 ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Adams Family Correspondence</span></span>, facing <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-03-02-0095#ADMS-04-03-02-pb-0116-04" class="pageNo">p. 117</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d229n2-ptr" id="PJA08d229n2">2</a>
       <p>An error for 32.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d229n3-ptr" id="PJA08d229n3">3</a>
       <p>That is, 27 varas. The vara, a Spanish unit of measurement, equaled approximately 33 inches (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Oxford English Dictionary,&lt;/i&gt; Oxford, 1933; 12 vols. and supplement. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">OED</span></span>).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d229n4-ptr" id="PJA08d229n4">4</a>
       <p>The correct figure is 299.75.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d229n5-ptr" id="PJA08d229n5">5</a>
       <p>Four thousand reals equals 500 pesos or, as they were also known, dollars. This is considerably more than the sum mentioned in the first paragraph of this letter, assuming that <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> had given his order in terms of dollars as the equivalent of pesos.</p>
      </div>
